Here is the solution. It's a key idea in many numerical algorithms to reduce a problem to unit scale. In this case, we use `std::minmax_element` function from `algorithm` library which does the same work as min and max but in a single sweep making effective use of CPU cache. The rescaling is done by subtracting min, dividing by max-min to get [0, 1] interval.

```cpp
#include <stdio.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

vector<float> rescale_to_unit(vector<float> numbers){
    const auto [min_it, max_it] = minmax_element(begin(numbers), end(numbers));

    const auto min_elem = *min_it;
    const auto scale = *max_it - min_elem;

    for(auto& value : numbers){
        value = (value - min_elem) / scale;
    }

    return numbers;
}
