The bubbleSort function itself uses two loops - one to traverse through the entire array, and another to compare each element with the next one. If the next element is smaller, the elements are swapped.

Bubble sort has a worst-case and average time complexity of O(n), where n is the number of items being sorted.  This makes the bubble sort well-suited to small or mostly sorted datasets.

